All Implemented Interfaces:
Order, Strategizable<TreeNode,TreeNode,BaseParameterAcceptStrategy<?>>
public final class BinaryTreeParameterAcceptStrategy extends BaseParameterAcceptStrategy<TreeNode>

BinaryTreeParameterAcceptStrategy is an parameter acceptance strategy used to accept TreeNode type and accept it to a binary tree as TreeNode instance.

    • acceptParameter

      protected TreeNode acceptParameter(Object object, Parameter type, Map<Class<?>,Set<BaseParameterAcceptStrategy<?>>> strategiesMap) throws Throwable
      Accept the object.
      Specified by:
      acceptParameter in class BaseParameterAcceptStrategy<TreeNode>
      Parameters:
      object - the object.
      type - the parameter type.
      strategiesMap - the strategies map that can be used during this accepting process.

      The key is the output object class to which this BaseParameterAcceptStrategy applies. The value is a set of strategy with the same accepted type. And the set is sorted the priority of Strategizable based on getOrder().

      Returns:
      the accepted parameter.
      Throws:
      Throwable
